The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Unions and the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions will form a strike commission on Friday to coordinate Monday’s strike that will last indefinitely.
A protest rally will take place on Saturday, while Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will take place - will begin unemployment.
This action will certainly cause great difficulties in transport, since rail traffic will be completely stopped and until 1 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Public Transport Company will also be on strike.
On Friday afternoon, the League Trade Unions will report on the details of their Monday strike to be held jointly with the National Federation of Workers’ Commissions.
The strike commission of the LIGA and the National Union of Engineers will also be formed, which will coordinate Monday’s actions.
A protest rally will take place on Saturday, while participating unions will strike indefinitely on Monday if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law, they did not report the date of the end of the strike.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their call to strike.
Instead, if the law is passed, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the Monday agenda of the National Assembly, it is also possible that only the public health law will be voted on in the very early hours of the night, or perhaps near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will begin on Monday, there will be significant difficulties in transport: on the railways will be stopped work indefinitely, in the morning some of the Budapest public transport and more than half of the intercity bus transport of the Volán companies may be stopped.
At the same time, in many parts of the country, half of the roads will be closed.
Numerous unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League website.
Some unions announced their strike for indefinite time, others for definite time.
Until Thursday afternoon, the State Railway and the Free Trade Union of Rail Workers (SLTF) were unable to reach an agreement even on minimum services, although as the Christmas holidays approach, more and more people travel on trains.
According to information received so far, from the start of the day until 1 p.m., the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company, the Budapest Airports will be on strike from 7 to 9 a.m., a four-hour strike will be held by the LIGA Trade Unions of the Electrical and Thermal Energy Industry, the Educators' Trade Unions called the Educators' 2 hours strike.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will strike at alternate hours and the Democratic Union of Health and Social Workers (SDTSSS) which are part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is for the government to withdraw its proposal on public health reform and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation that will come into effect next year.
The third is to ensure that, even before 2010, in the case of advance pensions, occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF), which is part of the League Trade Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the rail sidelines and expect another different proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: In the country the risk is increased by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from several points of view.
The company’s “risk warning” states: “In relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is the fact that with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy populations of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes may occur.”
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy is probably the provocation of an event of this character," added the representative of the research institute.
They affirmed that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the gypsies problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the differences between gypsies and Hungarians".
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "deteriorated significantly the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country".
They remind us that: since autumn 2006 the reorganization of the radical and far-right groups in Hungary has received increasing publicity and momentum, and that since summer 2007 numerous self-defining organisations have been established in the country as "national self-defense associations".
"The common feature of these groups is that they define themselves as civilian organizations, while openly proclaiming the training of their members for defense - even armed - (civil defense, national defense, defense of public order), alluding to the ineptitudes of the police, the army, i.e. the state," they add.
They affirmed: all this occurs in accordance with the method that tries to give a civil presentation to different political aspirations, based on the discontent of society with politics and with political parties.
For highlighting the civil and the form of association in the case of these associations not only serves to avoid the legal problems of legal registration, but at the same time is also a political strategy.
