The Mifid, which amends the Securities Market Act, involves the modernization of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promoting cooperation between the various supervisors of the European Union.
The new regulation will provide financial advisory services to specialized firms as well as to natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory firms (FIs), which join securities companies, securities agencies and holding companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are joined by multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with existing exchange managers.
The Act also obliges investment firms to disclose information on the market on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all transactions they perform, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its passage through the Congressional Economics Commission, several modifications were incorporated, including that securitized debts are considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high danger to the investor, which has been proven with what happened with the U.S. high-risk mortgage debt (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that can be carried out by graduates in Economics and Business 30 years after the passing of the Royal Decree in 1977 delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the mediator, who will work for another person, will not require the authorization of the CNMV and will be able to provide its products marketing and customer acquisition services to different investment companies at the same time.
