A change in the American People’s Bankruptcy Act (2005) resulted in a sharp drop in bankruptcy applications, which in turn represent a huge loss in credit cards; the number of applications (and therefore, of delinquency) would be growing again, or it may happen that conditions for borrowers were worsening.
