It's not the wooden boxes.
Who links the terms Sweden and wooden box, thinks of Ikea, but does not think of Andy Warhol.
Or is it?
Today the wooden boxes produced in Sweden are like the shadow that weighs on Warhol’s list of works.
Most of the ninety-four "type" Brightness-Boxes on this list are fake.
After a few months ago the Swedish newspaper "Expressen" questioned the authenticity of Andy Warhol's 1968 Bright-Boxes, the Moderna Museum in Stockholm conducted internal investigations and came to disappointing conclusions: the six "Bright-Boxes", which the former director of the Pontus Hultén museum gave to the other ones in the Moderna Museum.
Prehistory is too complicated with a confusing relationship between artistic and sponsored productions.
In 1964 Warhol created his first "Bright-Boxes" in New York, painted the wooden boxes in red, blue and white, with the same sample that had "Bright" soap powder cartons.
According to Warhol, in the exhibition of his works from 1968 at the Modern Museum were exposed hundreds of Bright cardboard boxes. These were not made by Warhol (because of the expenses), but were brought directly from the "Bright" cardboard factory.
They were not works of art, but specimens (which were only objects) exhibited.
In the same year, 1968, Warhol allowed to produce in Sweden some Bright wooden boxes, but they were not exhibited at the Modern Museet.
Witnesses of that time now speak of nearly fifteen boxes, which at that time entered the history of art and auctions as originals of the "Bright-Boxes" of the "Stockholm type" authorized by Andy Warhol.
At auctions some of them were bought for more than $100,000.
The problem is that after the famous director of the Pontus Hultén museum made false statements that in 1968 in Sweden almost one hundred of the wooden boxes that Warhol left to him were produced and exposed.
But in reality, 105 boxes were produced in the same year 1990 in Malmö for Hultén and for the exhibition in St. Petersburg.
At this time Warhol had already died for 3 years.
Lars Byström, the head of the conservators of the Modern Museum, investigated six Bright Boxes owned by the museum and also three of the Swedish private property that were manufactured in 1968 in Stockholm.
On the contrary, the structure of the copies of 1990 shows that the paint was applied with a roller without directly printing the tightened silvers. Besides it is not oil paint, but acrylic paint.
“These boxes have not been authorized by the artist and must be removed from the official list of Andy Warhol’s Bright Boxes,” says Lars Nittve, the director of the Modern Museum and adds that if the Authentication Commission “Andy Warhol Art” in New York will not come to any conclusion, the Modern Museum will classify these six boxes as the copies/objects of the exhibition.
As early as July, the Authentication Commission formally announced that it accepts these "serious allegations" that they are boxes of soap dust.
But from that moment on everything remained in absolute silence.
The rebel soldiers surrender in Manila.
In the Philippines, rebel soldiers have surrendered who had entrenched themselves in a hotel in Manila and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Chief Antonio Trillanes, who blames the president for corruption and electoral fraud, told a reporter that he could not answer for bloodshed.
Government-faithful soldiers had raided the hotel using tear gas.
Almost two hundred soldiers had been entrenched in the building for a few hours.
Almost half of them, including Trillanes, had trial on Thursday for attempting a coup in 2003 that ended in failure.
He took advantage of the negotiations, in order to suddenly be able to deposit with about 30 sympathizers.
Evidently, the military police officers who were to watch him had passed into his ranks and followed his mutiny.
They entered the "Peninsula" hotel and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government troops blocked the neighborhood around the Hotel Noble.
The president called for an urgent meeting of the Security Office.
Norberto Gonzales, the national security adviser, condemned the behavior of the soldiers.
“People are fed up,” Trillanes said.
“We call on people to come into our ranks.”
General Danilo Lim, who previously headed the elite Scout Reangers troop, said that soon the other military troops wanted to continue the march.
Big government critics called Thursday for a big rally against the president.
For months, his government has been accused of corruption.
In 2003 the financial district in Manila was a site that attracted all the attention for the mutiny that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986, there have been at least seven attempted coups against the democratically elected government in the Philippines.
